CI workflow that publishes the project's visualization to GitHub Pages. Triggers on push to `main` or manual `workflow_dispatch`.

Build job: checks out repo, installs the Rust toolchain via `rustup show` (so it depends on a pinned toolchain file — likely `rust-toolchain.toml` — existing at repo root), runs `cargo run --bin viz-data` to regenerate `out/viz-data.json`, then assembles a `_site` directory containing `viz/index.html` and `out/viz-data.json` and uploads it as a Pages artifact. Deploy job consumes that artifact and publishes via `actions/deploy-pages@v4`.

Coupling: assumes a binary target named `viz-data` exists in the crate and that it writes its output to `out/viz-data.json` — if that binary is renamed or its output path changes, this workflow silently breaks (job would fail at the `cp` step). Also assumes `viz/index.html` expects to fetch a sibling `viz-data.json` at `out/viz-data.json` relative to the deployed site — the directory layout (`viz/` and `out/` both under site root) must match whatever path `viz/index.html` hardcodes for fetching the JSON. `permissions` and `concurrency: group: pages` are required by GitHub's official Pages deploy action pattern; removing them breaks deployment auth or causes concurrent-deploy races.